FBIS4-36641 "drnes113_j_94009" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Southern Official Rejects North's Territorial Claims Southern Official Rejects North's Territorial Claims EA1006193094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in English 1600 GMT 10 Jun 94 EA1006193094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in English 1600 GMT 10 Jun 94 English BFN [Text] Mr. Ahmad Sa'id al-Suraymah, the governor of Shabwah Governorate and the commander of the Shabwah Governorate military axis, refuted the declaration by the Sanaa regime that its forces are in control of 90 percent of Yemeni land. Al-Suraymah commented that this applies to the Yemen Arab Republic land. He told the YEMENI NEWS AGENCY, Aden, that the Democratic Republic of Yemen's forces are controlling 90 percent of the Shabwah Governorate, which the Sanaa military regime had wanted to occupy. He affirmed that our Armed Forces and the hero people of Shabwah had turned the aggressors away, after inflicting on them heavy casualties.
